Citation.sAbstract: Heat capacity measurements of K3Nb3O6(BO3)2, a borate that exhibits superionic conductivity and ferroelectric properties, have been performed in the 60 220K temperature range. In this work, the presence of two heat capacity anomalies has been documented. The first anomaly occurs at 198.3K and it has been attributed to a first-order phase transition. The second anomaly suggests presence of second-order phase transition at around 80 K.
Citation.sTitle: Heat capacity studies of phase transitions in K3Nb3O6(BO3)2
